WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.918 --> 00:00:05.045
{\an8}[♪ country music playing]

2
00:00:05.046 --> 00:00:06.548
{\an8}<i>♪ Sky ♪</i>

3
00:00:08.174 --> 00:00:11.720
<i>♪ You're just a place to fly ♪</i>

4
00:00:13.221 --> 00:00:16.890
<i>♪ You're just a big blue eyes ♪</i>

5
00:00:16.891 --> 00:00:18.600
[sign rattles]

6
00:00:18.601 --> 00:00:21.938
<i>♪ Like me sometimes you cry ♪</i>

7
00:00:23.940 --> 00:00:27.193
<i>♪ Looking for a home ♪</i>

8
00:00:30.530 --> 00:00:34.199
<i>♪ Sea ♪</i>

9
00:00:34.200 --> 00:00:37.912
<i>♪ You're nothing more to me ♪</i>

10
00:00:39.205 --> 00:00:43.293
<i>♪ Then just the rolling sea ♪</i>

11
00:00:44.294 --> 00:00:48.590
<i>♪ Another part of me ♪</i>

12
00:00:52.635 --> 00:00:54.428
[Teddi] <i>We've got nothing for you nearby.</i>

13
00:00:54.429 --> 00:00:56.597
- Look a little further out.
- [Velma] <i>Yeah. sure.</i>

14
00:00:56.598 --> 00:00:58.891
- Something will pop.
- Always does.

15
00:00:58.892 --> 00:01:01.185
- [car approaches]
- Let me know when you find something.

16
00:01:01.186 --> 00:01:02.520
[Teddi] <i>Sure thing.</i>

17
00:01:07.817 --> 00:01:09.486
[♪ tense music playing]

18
00:01:18.161 --> 00:01:19.162
[car door opens]

19
00:01:22.248 --> 00:01:23.249
[door closes]

20
00:01:38.973 --> 00:01:39.974
Hey. little brother.

21
00:01:42.435 --> 00:01:45.814
You gonna shoot me.
or can we sit down and have a few?

22
00:01:46.606 --> 00:01:47.899
I brought some of my homebrew.

23
00:01:56.825 --> 00:01:58.827
[♪ ominous music playing]

24
00:02:11.172 --> 00:02:13.757
Guess this is one of those
who's-gonna-go-first deals. huh?

25
00:02:13.758 --> 00:02:16.135
- You called me.
- True.

26
00:02:16.136 --> 00:02:18.387
- You called people I work with.
- Also true.

27
00:02:18.388 --> 00:02:21.974
I set up a time and a day
to meet last week. and you don't show.

28
00:02:21.975 --> 00:02:23.434
Sorry about that.

29
00:02:28.940 --> 00:02:30.149
That it?

30
00:02:30.150 --> 00:02:32.610
- Well. something came up.
- "Something came up."

31
00:02:33.778 --> 00:02:35.779
What's so important. Russell.
you keep calling me?

32
00:02:35.780 --> 00:02:38.241
Dory thinks we ought
to put the past behind us.

33
00:02:39.033 --> 00:02:41.119
I tried months ago. You blew me off.

34
00:02:43.830 --> 00:02:44.831
So let's get to it.

35
00:02:47.333 --> 00:02:49.586
I know you think
I pushed Dad off that cliff.

36
00:02:51.379 --> 00:02:52.380
I saw you there.

37
00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:57.010
Colter. I didn't push him.

38
00:02:58.219 --> 00:02:59.678
I don't know if he fell.

39
00:02:59.679 --> 00:03:01.972
or if somebody else pushed him.

40
00:03:01.973 --> 00:03:04.767
but I do know there was somebody else
in those woods that night.

41
00:03:05.727 --> 00:03:07.144
Dad had enemies. Colter.

42
00:03:07.145 --> 00:03:09.188
He was a crazy son of a bitch.

43
00:03:09.189 --> 00:03:10.899
He was paranoid.

44
00:03:11.482 --> 00:03:12.984
The man was hard as hell on us.

45
00:03:14.110 --> 00:03:15.694
Making us learn how to skin a rabbit?

46
00:03:15.695 --> 00:03:17.864
Not exactly a skill I need these days.

47
00:03:20.033 --> 00:03:21.075
[scoffs]

48
00:03:24.245 --> 00:03:26.455
Why would Mom let me believe
that you did it?

49
00:03:26.456 --> 00:03:27.748
Yeah. I don't know.

50
00:03:27.749 --> 00:03:29.917
I like to think she did
the best she could.

51
00:03:29.918 --> 00:03:31.668
But Mom had her secrets. trust me.

52
00:03:31.669 --> 00:03:33.963
You can't drop that on me
and not explain yourself.

53
00:03:34.756 --> 00:03:37.090
The man I saw in the woods
the night Dad died.

54
00:03:37.091 --> 00:03:38.676
I'd seen him once before.

55
00:03:42.222 --> 00:03:43.765
I saw him talking to our mom.

56
00:03:44.432 --> 00:03:46.476
Are you saying
Mom had something to do with this?

57
00:03:48.895 --> 00:03:49.896
I-I don't know.

58
00:03:51.856 --> 00:03:54.859
But when Dad died.
she said it would be best if I left.

59
00:03:56.903 --> 00:03:58.905
and to keep quiet about what happened.

60
00:04:01.991 --> 00:04:03.242
You didn't question that?

61
00:04:03.243 --> 00:04:04.868
She said our lives depended on it.

62
00:04:04.869 --> 00:04:06.495
Because of what happened to Dad?

63
00:04:06.496 --> 00:04:08.288
I was a kid. so I left.

64
00:04:08.289 --> 00:04:10.916
And then I got a little older
and I just stayed gone.

65
00:04:10.917 --> 00:04:13.252
- You joined the military.
- Yeah. I enlisted.

66
00:04:13.253 --> 00:04:16.005
I thought that was the best way
to leave it all behind.

67
00:04:21.636 --> 00:04:24.638
Look. man. there's nothing
that we can say or do to bring Dad back

68
00:04:24.639 --> 00:04:26.390
or to make up for lost time. okay?

69
00:04:26.391 --> 00:04:27.641
What happened happened.

70
00:04:27.642 --> 00:04:29.227
Yeah. well. then. you know...

71
00:04:31.688 --> 00:04:32.939
I guess we're done here. right?

72
00:04:34.649 --> 00:04:36.191
[Russell scoffs]

73
00:04:36.192 --> 00:04:37.360
That it?

74
00:04:39.237 --> 00:04:40.570
I thought this'd be two brothers

75
00:04:40.571 --> 00:04:42.155
burying the old family hatchet.

76
00:04:42.156 --> 00:04:43.323
you know. hugging it out.

77
00:04:43.324 --> 00:04:45.576
You gave me a lot to think about.
didn't you?

78
00:04:46.577 --> 00:04:48.203
While you're doing your thinking.

79
00:04:48.204 --> 00:04:50.706
there's something
I could use your help with.

80
00:04:50.707 --> 00:04:53.542
- You find people. right? For rewards?
- Yeah.

81
00:04:53.543 --> 00:04:56.586
I'm trying to find an old unit
buddy of mine. Doug Thompson.

82
00:04:56.587 --> 00:04:59.673
- What happened?
- He's been missing for five days.

83
00:04:59.674 --> 00:05:02.302
Wife said he left on an errand
and never came back.

84
00:05:03.386 --> 00:05:05.846
That's why I missed our meeting.
I was checking things out.

85
00:05:05.847 --> 00:05:08.307
- Problems in the marriage?
- No. Doug's a solid guy.

86
00:05:08.308 --> 00:05:10.100
He wouldn't...

87
00:05:10.101 --> 00:05:11.394
He wouldn't ditch Tracy.

88
00:05:12.270 --> 00:05:13.895
Anything else you can
give me to go on?

89
00:05:13.896 --> 00:05:16.691
I traced his phone
to a gas station outside of Roanoke.

90
00:05:17.650 --> 00:05:21.195
It was in the trash. it was all busted up.
His car was still there.

91
00:05:22.155 --> 00:05:24.115
- Gas stations have cameras.
- They do.

92
00:05:24.657 --> 00:05:28.494
Doug was on the surveillance video
until he bolted off cam.

93
00:05:29.245 --> 00:05:30.830
He was acting real sketchy.

94
00:05:31.331 --> 00:05:32.665
Something was wrong.

95
00:05:35.501 --> 00:05:37.794
I can pay you. you know.
for your help.

96
00:05:37.795 --> 00:05:40.798
Russell. it's not about the money.

97
00:05:45.678 --> 00:05:46.971
Will you help me. or no?

98
00:05:50.350 --> 00:05:51.392
Yeah. I'll help you.

99
00:05:53.853 --> 00:05:55.355
Great. Thanks.

100
00:06:00.443 --> 00:06:03.028
[♪ country music playing
on car stereo]

101
00:06:03.029 --> 00:06:06.866
<i>♪ Name one day and I followed
that voice down the lost highway ♪</i>

102
00:06:20.421 --> 00:06:22.089
Here you go.

103
00:06:22.090 --> 00:06:23.925
Free coffee from the lobby.

104
00:06:24.467 --> 00:06:25.467
Free coffee?

105
00:06:25.468 --> 00:06:27.303
Yeah. It does the trick. Trust me.

106
00:06:28.846 --> 00:06:30.806
- Living here?
- Yeah. for now.

107
00:06:30.807 --> 00:06:33.558
It's not that bad.
They actually got a hot tub in the back.

108
00:06:33.559 --> 00:06:35.477
Met a girl from Tallahassee
the other night.

109
00:06:35.478 --> 00:06:37.562
Used to be a cheerleader.
Like a pro one.

110
00:06:37.563 --> 00:06:40.107
Yeah. she's a dental hygienist now.

111
00:06:40.108 --> 00:06:42.359
I'm sure this story has a point.
but we should go.

112
00:06:42.360 --> 00:06:45.362
Listen. I wanted to ask you.
We're good. right?

113
00:06:45.363 --> 00:06:48.156
You believe me
about what I said about Dad?

114
00:06:48.157 --> 00:06:50.992
Uh. you know. I don't know
what to believe right now.

115
00:06:50.993 --> 00:06:53.412
Let's go to your friend's. okay?

116
00:06:53.413 --> 00:06:54.831
Let's go.

117
00:06:55.957 --> 00:06:57.959
[engine starts]

118
00:07:04.799 --> 00:07:07.926
- You gonna tell me about your friend or...
- Sure. Doug Thompson.

119
00:07:07.927 --> 00:07:11.054
He's one of the good ones.
Saved my life more than once.

120
00:07:11.055 --> 00:07:13.099
I owe him. He's. you know. family to me.

121
00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:16.518
You guys go back a ways then. huh?

122
00:07:16.519 --> 00:07:18.937
- Served 18 years together. Same unit.
- Then what?

123
00:07:18.938 --> 00:07:21.523
- After that?
- I don't know. we got out.

124
00:07:21.524 --> 00:07:24.025
We kept in touch.
Ran in the same crowd. You know?

125
00:07:24.026 --> 00:07:25.152
I don't know.

126
00:07:25.153 --> 00:07:28.113
To help you find this guy.
you'll have to give me something.

127
00:07:28.114 --> 00:07:29.573
I need to know his routine.

128
00:07:29.574 --> 00:07:31.074
What's this guy about? Come on.

129
00:07:31.075 --> 00:07:32.367
[chuckles]

130
00:07:32.368 --> 00:07:33.910
All right. Um...

131
00:07:33.911 --> 00:07:35.579
Doug's quiet.

132
00:07:35.580 --> 00:07:38.707
You know. he's...
Some people might say he's intense.

133
00:07:38.708 --> 00:07:42.461
I hooked him up with this outfit.
civilian contract stuff.

134
00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:44.004
And that's what you do. too?

135
00:07:44.005 --> 00:07:47.299
Yeah. it's what most of us
ex-special ops guys do.

136
00:07:47.300 --> 00:07:50.635
We miss the excitement
when we transition to civilian life.

137
00:07:50.636 --> 00:07:51.845
And it pays very well.

138
00:07:51.846 --> 00:07:53.472
What's the name of this outfit?

139
00:07:53.473 --> 00:07:56.476
The Horizon Group. but I don't think
it has anything to do with them.

140
00:07:57.560 --> 00:07:58.768
What makes you say that?

141
00:07:58.769 --> 00:08:01.438
Doug got into a car accident
about six weeks ago. Okay?

142
00:08:01.439 --> 00:08:03.231
Nothing major. but it shook him up.

143
00:08:03.232 --> 00:08:05.400
and he started acting weird.
getting paranoid.

144
00:08:05.401 --> 00:08:09.446
So I'm thinking maybe he got a concussion
that triggered some PTSD.

145
00:08:09.447 --> 00:08:10.947
and I don't know.

146
00:08:10.948 --> 00:08:13.993
maybe he got scared
and he ran off and he's hiding somewhere.

147
00:08:14.869 --> 00:08:15.870
Maybe.

148
00:08:17.121 --> 00:08:18.121
This is it.

149
00:08:18.122 --> 00:08:19.415
- Last house on the right there.
- Yeah.

150
00:08:21.876 --> 00:08:23.878
[♪ tense music playing]

151
00:08:26.464 --> 00:08:27.507
[knocking on door]

152
00:08:28.716 --> 00:08:32.345
Tracy. hey. this is Colter.
He's gonna help us find Doug.

153
00:08:34.680 --> 00:08:36.182
What is it? What happened?

154
00:08:36.891 --> 00:08:39.100
There was a package
on my porch this morning.

155
00:08:39.101 --> 00:08:41.354
- Mind if we take a look?
- Come in.

156
00:08:45.149 --> 00:08:46.692
- Have a seat.
- Thanks.

157
00:08:57.078 --> 00:08:59.038
- When was it delivered?
- An hour ago.

158
00:09:06.963 --> 00:09:09.464
- You call the police?
- No. I waited for you.

159
00:09:09.465 --> 00:09:11.216
You think this might belong to Doug?

160
00:09:11.217 --> 00:09:13.302
I don't know.
Why would someone send that to me?

161
00:09:14.512 --> 00:09:15.762
- Was there a note?
- Nothing.

162
00:09:15.763 --> 00:09:17.806
You have security cameras outside?

163
00:09:17.807 --> 00:09:20.351
We did. but Doug disabled them.

164
00:09:21.269 --> 00:09:25.314
He was worried that people might
hack into the network. spy on us.

165
00:09:26.107 --> 00:09:28.900
He's been a little off lately.
he thought people were watching him.

166
00:09:28.901 --> 00:09:30.026
He say who?

167
00:09:30.027 --> 00:09:31.444
No.

168
00:09:31.445 --> 00:09:33.446
Do you have any idea why Doug's car

169
00:09:33.447 --> 00:09:35.991
would have been found
at a gas station outside of town?

170
00:09:35.992 --> 00:09:39.077
No. he was just supposed to pick up
groceries at the market.

171
00:09:39.078 --> 00:09:40.829
He didn't mention anything to me either.

172
00:09:40.830 --> 00:09:43.331
- Maybe this is about Horizon?
- We don't know yet.

173
00:09:43.332 --> 00:09:46.251
He doesn't tell me anything about
what he does or who he works for.

174
00:09:46.252 --> 00:09:47.711
Because he can't.

175
00:09:47.712 --> 00:09:50.130
He can't. You know that.

176
00:09:50.131 --> 00:09:52.507
I just want to know he's okay.

177
00:09:52.508 --> 00:09:54.594
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

178
00:09:57.430 --> 00:09:59.265
I'm gonna help you find your husband.

179
00:10:03.894 --> 00:10:06.063
- What's this? What are we doing?
- I'll show you.

180
00:10:08.065 --> 00:10:09.150
Help me out. will ya?

181
00:10:11.861 --> 00:10:13.320
Fill that in for me.

182
00:10:13.321 --> 00:10:15.155
Is this some sort of homemade psych exam?

183
00:10:15.156 --> 00:10:18.366
- I can save you the trouble.
- [scoffs] I know you're crazy.

184
00:10:18.367 --> 00:10:21.787
I'll try to pull a print off this finger.
see if it belongs to Doug.

185
00:10:23.539 --> 00:10:24.873
Eh...

186
00:10:24.874 --> 00:10:26.959
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

187
00:10:29.003 --> 00:10:30.086
That's good enough.

188
00:10:30.087 --> 00:10:32.214
Piece of tape. a couple inches.

189
00:10:37.428 --> 00:10:38.638
Great.

190
00:10:44.310 --> 00:10:45.478
There you go.

191
00:10:49.607 --> 00:10:52.233
- [scoffs]
- Something Dad didn't teach us. right?

192
00:10:52.234 --> 00:10:53.319
Son of a bitch.

193
00:10:53.986 --> 00:10:55.278
[shutter clicks]

194
00:10:55.279 --> 00:10:57.697
- Now what are you doing?
- I gotta send this to my guy.

195
00:10:57.698 --> 00:10:59.658
- What? You got a guy?
- I got a guy.

196
00:10:59.659 --> 00:11:02.035
Sort of like an op analyst. if you will.

197
00:11:02.036 --> 00:11:04.120
You got an op analyst
for your rewardist hustle?

198
00:11:04.121 --> 00:11:07.082
- Oh. it's not a hustle.
- Right. Okay.

199
00:11:07.083 --> 00:11:11.045
This. uh. this work you're doing with
Doug and Horizon. Tell me about it.

200
00:11:12.171 --> 00:11:13.588
Private security. Mostly.

201
00:11:13.589 --> 00:11:15.006
Every job's a little different.

202
00:11:15.007 --> 00:11:16.675
- Off the books stuff?
- Oh. yeah.

203
00:11:16.676 --> 00:11:19.928
Why does Doug's wife think
his disappearance is related to Horizon?

204
00:11:19.929 --> 00:11:22.514
Tracy hates the fact
that Doug still does this work.

205
00:11:22.515 --> 00:11:23.848
She'd rather him. I don't know.

206
00:11:23.849 --> 00:11:25.809
sell insurance.
something normal like that.

207
00:11:25.810 --> 00:11:26.893
That's not Doug's speed.

208
00:11:26.894 --> 00:11:28.853
Last time you talked to him.
he seemed normal?

209
00:11:28.854 --> 00:11:29.979
I wouldn't say normal.

210
00:11:29.980 --> 00:11:32.232
He brought up
some old mission from Yemen.

211
00:11:32.233 --> 00:11:33.692
- With Horizon?
- No.

212
00:11:33.693 --> 00:11:37.153
No. it was about 10 years before that
with our old special ops unit.

213
00:11:37.154 --> 00:11:38.571
And why would he bring that up?

214
00:11:38.572 --> 00:11:39.823
I don't know.

215
00:11:39.824 --> 00:11:41.784
[phone buzzing]

216
00:11:42.910 --> 00:11:44.537
- Hey. Bobby.
- Is that your analyst?

217
00:11:45.204 --> 00:11:46.580
- [Bobby] <i>Who's that?</i>
- My brother.

218
00:11:47.206 --> 00:11:49.667
- Damn. for real?
- I'm guessing Colter hasn't mentioned me.

219
00:11:50.835 --> 00:11:51.918
<i>No. he didn't.</i>

220
00:11:51.919 --> 00:11:53.753
What do you got for me. Bobby?

221
00:11:53.754 --> 00:11:55.839
Right. I put a face to your finger.

222
00:11:55.840 --> 00:11:58.675
Name's Len Klavens.
Matched his prints to police records.

223
00:11:58.676 --> 00:12:00.218
Sending it to you now.

224
00:12:00.219 --> 00:12:01.386
[text chimes]

225
00:12:01.387 --> 00:12:04.222
- [Russell] That was fast.
- What was he arrested for?

226
00:12:04.223 --> 00:12:07.058
Nothing serious.
Public loitering. Multiple times.

227
00:12:07.059 --> 00:12:09.394
- Is he homeless?
<i>- In and out of rehabs.</i>

228
00:12:09.395 --> 00:12:11.312
Now he's in Roanoke city morgue.

229
00:12:11.313 --> 00:12:12.732
<i>Died two days ago.</i>

230
00:12:14.066 --> 00:12:15.735
- We gotta see that body.
- Yep.

231
00:12:24.618 --> 00:12:26.619
[♪ jaunty music playing]

232
00:12:26.620 --> 00:12:28.330
[keyboard clacking]

233
00:12:29.874 --> 00:12:30.875
I got this.

234
00:12:31.459 --> 00:12:32.917
What can I help you with?

235
00:12:32.918 --> 00:12:34.754
Hi. Um...

236
00:12:35.546 --> 00:12:36.546
"Yolanda."

237
00:12:36.547 --> 00:12:38.466
Oh. that is a...
That's a beautiful name.

238
00:12:39.550 --> 00:12:42.218
Sadly. we. uh. we heard about Len Klavens.

239
00:12:42.219 --> 00:12:45.264
recently deceased. and. uh.
we just need to see the body.

240
00:12:45.765 --> 00:12:46.766
What for?

241
00:12:47.975 --> 00:12:50.268
How do you like working here. huh?

242
00:12:50.269 --> 00:12:51.895
I get a good vibe from you.

243
00:12:51.896 --> 00:12:54.063
Kind eyes. helpful eyes. I like that.

244
00:12:54.064 --> 00:12:55.900
[scoffs] What's he talking about?

245
00:12:59.320 --> 00:13:00.695
The body might be connected

246
00:13:00.696 --> 00:13:02.238
to the disappearance of another man.

247
00:13:02.239 --> 00:13:05.868
Oh. sorry. but unless you're family.
I can't let you back there.

248
00:13:06.744 --> 00:13:08.913
I didn't mention. Cousins.

249
00:13:11.999 --> 00:13:14.501
We just... We just need a minute to.
you know...

250
00:13:14.502 --> 00:13:16.461
Promise we won't disrupt a thing.

251
00:13:16.462 --> 00:13:20.089
And then afterwards. maybe.
uh. we go grab a drink

252
00:13:20.090 --> 00:13:22.009
or. uh. somethin'-somethin'?

253
00:13:25.513 --> 00:13:27.097
No. Sorry.

254
00:13:28.349 --> 00:13:30.184
- That was so close.
- No.

255
00:13:31.310 --> 00:13:33.353
I can't believe "kind eyes" didn't work.

256
00:13:33.354 --> 00:13:36.356
I didn't see you stepping up.
You got a better idea?

257
00:13:36.357 --> 00:13:37.441
I might.

258
00:13:40.277 --> 00:13:42.279
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

259
00:13:52.331 --> 00:13:53.498
Okay.

260
00:13:53.499 --> 00:13:54.875
Whoa. whoa.

261
00:13:55.793 --> 00:13:56.794
Okay.

262
00:14:02.508 --> 00:14:03.508
You coming?

263
00:14:03.509 --> 00:14:05.009
[grunts]

264
00:14:05.010 --> 00:14:06.845
- Put your foot on the...
- I got it. I got it.

265
00:14:06.846 --> 00:14:07.930
There you go.

266
00:14:18.065 --> 00:14:19.274
[doorknob rattles]

267
00:14:19.275 --> 00:14:20.359
Great.

268
00:14:21.235 --> 00:14:23.863
[Russell] Ah. multi-tool. Cool.

269
00:14:25.447 --> 00:14:27.366
- Slide it in the frame now.
- Yup.

270
00:14:28.742 --> 00:14:29.743
Here it comes.

271
00:14:32.121 --> 00:14:33.122
Nice.

272
00:14:34.290 --> 00:14:35.708
Thank you.

273
00:14:40.045 --> 00:14:42.130
- You sure there's no alarm?
- You hear an alarm?

274
00:14:42.131 --> 00:14:43.756
No. Just. it seems easy.

275
00:14:43.757 --> 00:14:45.885
Don't get me wrong. I'll take the win.

276
00:14:57.605 --> 00:14:58.606
Here we go.

277
00:15:01.817 --> 00:15:03.402
- [Russell] This is him.
- Yeah.

278
00:15:22.504 --> 00:15:23.756
- Check the hand.
- Yeah.

279
00:15:28.052 --> 00:15:29.969
- Mutilated.
- That's weird.

280
00:15:29.970 --> 00:15:31.805
You ever seen anything like this before?

281
00:15:34.475 --> 00:15:35.558
- [officer] Freeze!
- Whoa!

282
00:15:35.559 --> 00:15:37.353
- All right.
- Keep those hands up!

283
00:15:42.858 --> 00:15:45.361
I meant what I said. you know?
Kind eyes.

284
00:15:48.739 --> 00:15:50.908
My offer for dinner still stands.

285
00:15:56.205 --> 00:15:58.456
How did you say
we were gonna get out of this?

286
00:15:58.457 --> 00:16:00.250
[sighs] Don't worry about it.

287
00:16:01.126 --> 00:16:04.504
Let's just think about this.
Who would send a finger to Doug's wife?

288
00:16:04.505 --> 00:16:06.172
- [footsteps approaching]
- Here we go.

289
00:16:06.173 --> 00:16:08.258
[♪ quirky music playing]

290
00:16:10.511 --> 00:16:12.096
Gentlemen. you're free.

291
00:16:13.430 --> 00:16:14.431
Time to go.

292
00:16:15.140 --> 00:16:18.643
You must be Russell Shaw.
Reenie Greene.

293
00:16:18.644 --> 00:16:21.020
- Oh. you didn't call me back.
- Sorry about that. Busy.

294
00:16:21.021 --> 00:16:23.731
{\an8}Working for Colter? Can't imagine
the things he's got you doing.

295
00:16:23.732 --> 00:16:27.110
{\an8}No. I do not work for him.
I work with him. honey. Get that straight.

296
00:16:27.111 --> 00:16:30.196
{\an8}And only sometimes.
and only when I get paid.

297
00:16:30.197 --> 00:16:31.864
{\an8}And trust me. I always get paid.

298
00:16:31.865 --> 00:16:33.199
{\an8}I bet you do.

299
00:16:33.200 --> 00:16:35.702
{\an8}[scoffs] You have an
interesting criminal record.

300
00:16:35.703 --> 00:16:37.537
{\an8}Disturbing the peace in Tuscaloosa

301
00:16:37.538 --> 00:16:39.497
{\an8}with a speedboat and a donkey?

302
00:16:39.498 --> 00:16:41.833
{\an8}- I wouldn't worry about that.
- Wasn't planning on it.

303
00:16:41.834 --> 00:16:45.129
{\an8}But you owe me for some unpaid fish
and wildlife fines I paid on your behalf.

304
00:16:45.713 --> 00:16:48.256
{\an8}Poaching. nice. You can Venmo me.

305
00:16:48.257 --> 00:16:51.259
{\an8}Thank you. But. uh. it wasn't poaching.
for the record.

306
00:16:51.260 --> 00:16:53.886
{\an8}- Are we. uh. being charged or not?
- No.

307
00:16:53.887 --> 00:16:56.514
{\an8}I persuaded the prosecutor
you were overcome with grief

308
00:16:56.515 --> 00:16:57.807
{\an8}and behaving irrationally.

309
00:16:57.808 --> 00:16:58.891
{\an8}- Thank you.
- Mmm-hmm.

310
00:16:58.892 --> 00:17:00.810
{\an8}Luckily. the prosecutor sympathized.

311
00:17:00.811 --> 00:17:04.565
{\an8}Said that he also had some problem clients
when he was a defense attorney.

312
00:17:05.941 --> 00:17:08.401
{\an8}- Fishing for compliments.
- I think she's awesome.

313
00:17:08.402 --> 00:17:11.195
- So how can we repay you?
- Besides the Venmo?

314
00:17:11.196 --> 00:17:14.700
You're gonna buy me lunch and tell me
everything that's been going on.

315
00:17:15.826 --> 00:17:17.035
{\an8}Okay.

316
00:17:17.036 --> 00:17:20.621
I know it's not fancy. but there's
nothing better than food off a truck.

317
00:17:20.622 --> 00:17:22.623
- It's not my first time.
- I'm sure it's not.

318
00:17:22.624 --> 00:17:25.043
Avert your eyes.
I'm a Sriracha-on-fries kinda guy.

319
00:17:25.044 --> 00:17:28.379
Also. for the record. it was not my idea
to break into the morgue.

320
00:17:28.380 --> 00:17:29.714
{\an8}[clicks tongue]

321
00:17:29.715 --> 00:17:32.843
{\an8}Doesn't surprise me.
What was so important about this body?

322
00:17:33.969 --> 00:17:36.637
{\an8}Someone sent a finger to Doug's wife.

323
00:17:36.638 --> 00:17:39.390
{\an8}Okay. was your morgue friend
connected to Doug?

324
00:17:39.391 --> 00:17:41.392
{\an8}You worked with him
for a long time. right?

325
00:17:41.393 --> 00:17:43.936
{\an8}- Look at you snooping on me.
- I wouldn't call it snooping.

326
00:17:43.937 --> 00:17:45.188
{\an8}"Deep dive" is more like it.

327
00:17:45.189 --> 00:17:46.314
Huh.

328
00:17:46.315 --> 00:17:49.067
The military. post military.
your extracurriculars.

329
00:17:49.068 --> 00:17:50.318
El Salvador.

330
00:17:50.319 --> 00:17:53.613
I'm curious about this employer
you and Doug work for.

331
00:17:53.614 --> 00:17:55.364
- The Horizon Group?
- Not much to tell.

332
00:17:55.365 --> 00:17:56.783
Checks clear. Good insurance.

333
00:17:56.784 --> 00:17:58.076
Doug's wife is suspicious.

334
00:17:58.077 --> 00:17:59.786
- but so far there's no connection.
- Uh-huh.

335
00:17:59.787 --> 00:18:02.497
Then I will reserve my judgment
until I do some digging.

336
00:18:02.498 --> 00:18:04.792
{\an8}- Knock yourself out.
- [phone buzzing]

337
00:18:05.918 --> 00:18:08.961
{\an8}Oh. balls. All right.
I got a lot going on at work.

338
00:18:08.962 --> 00:18:11.130
{\an8}You guys have fun.

339
00:18:11.131 --> 00:18:13.508
{\an8}Be careful.
and I'll catch up with you later.

340
00:18:13.509 --> 00:18:15.302
{\an8}- [Colter] All right.
- [Reenie] Bye.

341
00:18:19.556 --> 00:18:22.851
{\an8}So I'm gonna need a sitrep on. uh.
the thing between you and her.

342
00:18:24.394 --> 00:18:25.770
{\an8}No situation to report.

343
00:18:25.771 --> 00:18:28.439
'Cause I think she is...
[clicks tongue] impressive.

344
00:18:28.440 --> 00:18:29.565
- Uh-huh.
- Thorough.

345
00:18:29.566 --> 00:18:32.027
- Saying she's fair game?
- I'm saying she's off limits.

346
00:18:32.653 --> 00:18:33.654
You sure?

347
00:18:36.156 --> 00:18:38.991
{\an8}Just messin' with you.
[laughs] Your face.

348
00:18:38.992 --> 00:18:41.744
{\an8}Hey. I got a... A little surprise for you.

349
00:18:41.745 --> 00:18:43.496
{\an8}I grabbed this from the morgue.

350
00:18:43.497 --> 00:18:45.164
{\an8}Good thing they didn't strip search us.

351
00:18:45.165 --> 00:18:48.209
So our guy died of suspected overdose.

352
00:18:48.210 --> 00:18:51.880
But the disarticulation
occurred pre-mortem.

353
00:18:52.673 --> 00:18:53.882
- Really?
- Really.

354
00:18:54.466 --> 00:18:55.925
Say there where the body was located?

355
00:18:55.926 --> 00:18:57.553
- You betcha.
- All right.

356
00:18:59.263 --> 00:19:01.265
[♪ intense music playing]

357
00:19:09.106 --> 00:19:10.898
Report said our fingerless body

358
00:19:10.899 --> 00:19:12.233
was found near these dumpsters.

359
00:19:12.234 --> 00:19:13.776
Yeah. if they dumped the body here.

360
00:19:13.777 --> 00:19:15.904
they weren't too concerned
with keeping it hidden.

361
00:19:17.072 --> 00:19:19.824
This new breed. they don't take the time
to do the job right.

362
00:19:19.825 --> 00:19:21.826
Back in the day. it's a...
It's a shovel.

363
00:19:21.827 --> 00:19:24.871
lime. a little acid. six feet. at least.

364
00:19:24.872 --> 00:19:25.955
Now... [blows raspberry]

365
00:19:25.956 --> 00:19:28.416
Maybe they didn't
feel the need to hide it.

366
00:19:28.417 --> 00:19:30.835
- Sloppy work.
- Hey. look. let's cut to it.

367
00:19:30.836 --> 00:19:32.253
Ever since we found that body.

368
00:19:32.254 --> 00:19:35.632
I get the sense that you know something
you're not sharing with me.

369
00:19:37.467 --> 00:19:40.553
There were some guys in my unit
that were. uh. pretty superstitious.

370
00:19:40.554 --> 00:19:43.472
Okay? Doug included.
They were into that woo-woo stuff.

371
00:19:43.473 --> 00:19:45.767
- The prayers and rituals.
- Body parts?

372
00:19:47.144 --> 00:19:50.104
Maybe. yeah. Blood magic. protection.

373
00:19:50.105 --> 00:19:53.816
In fact. I heard there was. uh.
somebody you could go to to get blessings.

374
00:19:53.817 --> 00:19:55.151
- Blessing?
- Mmm-hmm.

375
00:19:55.152 --> 00:19:56.235
Was Doug into that?

376
00:19:56.236 --> 00:19:58.112
He said a few things now I think about it.

377
00:19:58.113 --> 00:20:00.239
There was this job we did in Peru.

378
00:20:00.240 --> 00:20:02.033
He brought me to this weird shrine.

379
00:20:02.034 --> 00:20:03.492
and we were giving offerings.

380
00:20:03.493 --> 00:20:05.494
Thought he was messing with me.
He was serious.

381
00:20:05.495 --> 00:20:06.746
In fact. he paid an old man

382
00:20:06.747 --> 00:20:08.956
to put a curse on one of our targets.

383
00:20:08.957 --> 00:20:10.041
- Huh.
- What?

384
00:20:10.042 --> 00:20:12.835
It's the same star and moon on the box
with the finger in it.

385
00:20:12.836 --> 00:20:15.088
- Oh.
- Let's go check it out.

386
00:20:22.763 --> 00:20:23.764
[door closes]

387
00:20:27.476 --> 00:20:28.601
What can I do for you?

388
00:20:28.602 --> 00:20:30.938
- Looking for some help.
- What sort of help?

389
00:20:32.481 --> 00:20:33.482
Protection.

390
00:20:33.982 --> 00:20:37.152
I think what my brother means
is a blessing. a strong one.

391
00:20:38.278 --> 00:20:41.239
- That's what you do here. right?
- It depends.

392
00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:42.950
How did you hear of our services?

393
00:20:44.743 --> 00:20:47.788
A friend said that this was the place.

394
00:20:50.582 --> 00:20:51.583
Follow me.

395
00:20:54.044 --> 00:20:56.046
[♪ intense rock music playing]

396
00:21:06.056 --> 00:21:07.807
I got your blessing.

397
00:21:07.808 --> 00:21:09.850
- Easy.
- We can do that.

398
00:21:09.851 --> 00:21:12.479
On your knees. cop.

399
00:21:12.938 --> 00:21:14.939
- [Russell] Hmm.
- You don't wanna do that.

400
00:21:14.940 --> 00:21:16.899
Like I said. get down.

401
00:21:16.900 --> 00:21:19.777
Listen. if you're gonna shoot.
shoot my brother first.

402
00:21:19.778 --> 00:21:21.737
Oh. come on.
Why would you do that?

403
00:21:21.738 --> 00:21:23.948
I'll shoot you both.
Sort out the parts later.

404
00:21:23.949 --> 00:21:27.119
- In that case. on three. Ready?
- [Colter and Russell] Three.

405
00:21:29.121 --> 00:21:30.789
Yeah. Here we go.

406
00:21:33.542 --> 00:21:34.542
What do you think. Colt?

407
00:21:34.543 --> 00:21:36.669
Shoot one. maybe. ask
the other one questions?

408
00:21:36.670 --> 00:21:38.254
We could start lopping digits.

409
00:21:38.255 --> 00:21:39.922
Start with a few toes. maybe.

410
00:21:39.923 --> 00:21:42.550
Please. We don't want any trouble.

411
00:21:42.551 --> 00:21:45.053
You've got trouble.
Looking for a friend of mine.

412
00:21:47.055 --> 00:21:48.056
Seen him?

413
00:21:49.057 --> 00:21:51.225
- Yeah.
- What was he doing here?

414
00:21:51.226 --> 00:21:53.477
He needed protection.
He was scared.

415
00:21:53.478 --> 00:21:54.603
He needed help.

416
00:21:54.604 --> 00:21:56.022
Well. he's missing.

417
00:21:56.023 --> 00:21:58.733
So whatever you were trying to
protect him from. it didn't work.

418
00:21:58.734 --> 00:22:01.485
How does this work?
You. uh. start cutting off fingers?

419
00:22:01.486 --> 00:22:04.113
- You kill that man?
- No. he overdosed.

420
00:22:04.114 --> 00:22:05.823
Why send the finger to the house?

421
00:22:05.824 --> 00:22:08.701
When something is asked.
it must be completed.

422
00:22:08.702 --> 00:22:12.204
He wanted a protective talisman
to keep his wife safe.

423
00:22:12.205 --> 00:22:14.749
- [Colter] Safe from what?
- He just gave us a name.

424
00:22:14.750 --> 00:22:16.208
Said this guy wanted to hurt him.

425
00:22:16.209 --> 00:22:19.211
- Let's have the name.
- That'll undo the blessing.

426
00:22:19.212 --> 00:22:22.298
Let me ask you this.
Is there a blessing

427
00:22:22.299 --> 00:22:25.843
that can keep me from squeezing
this trigger and blowing your face off?

428
00:22:25.844 --> 00:22:28.764
He'll do it. I've seen him do it.

429
00:22:29.514 --> 00:22:30.766
Give me the name.

430
00:22:32.434 --> 00:22:33.769
Give me the name.

431
00:22:35.687 --> 00:22:39.232
Solano. Carlos Solano.

432
00:22:48.325 --> 00:22:50.534
Solano. You've heard that name before?

433
00:22:50.535 --> 00:22:53.454
- Why was Doug afraid of that name?
- It's impossible.

434
00:22:53.455 --> 00:22:55.248
Doug and I did a job in Panama.

435
00:22:55.832 --> 00:22:57.500
For this Horizon contractor?

436
00:22:57.501 --> 00:23:00.169
Yeah. The mission was
to neutralize the target.

437
00:23:00.170 --> 00:23:02.839
- Kill?
- Health alteration. as we like to call it.

438
00:23:03.715 --> 00:23:04.882
Who was the target?

439
00:23:04.883 --> 00:23:07.385
It was a businessman named Moy Solano.

440
00:23:07.386 --> 00:23:09.512
Doug made the kill.
Getting out was a problem.

441
00:23:09.513 --> 00:23:12.139
That's what this is about?
Revenge for a botched job?

442
00:23:12.140 --> 00:23:14.975
Wasn't botched.
Solano's dead. I watched him drop.

443
00:23:14.976 --> 00:23:16.811
- They made you.
- Not me. They made Doug.

444
00:23:16.812 --> 00:23:18.687
He had to go back to the kill spot

445
00:23:18.688 --> 00:23:21.440
and Moy Solano's men saw him
and snapped a picture.

446
00:23:21.441 --> 00:23:23.609
Hold... Hold on a second.
Why did he go back?

447
00:23:23.610 --> 00:23:25.529
It was my fault. It was on me.

448
00:23:26.363 --> 00:23:28.823
I left something at the kill site.
I dropped my knife.

449
00:23:28.824 --> 00:23:31.409
I had to reach the extraction point.
so he went back.

450
00:23:31.410 --> 00:23:32.660
Why didn't Doug come to you?

451
00:23:32.661 --> 00:23:35.413
Thought he'd deal with it
or didn't wanna flag it with Horizon.

452
00:23:35.414 --> 00:23:37.540
- Kept a lot of people in dark.
- Well. that's Doug.

453
00:23:37.541 --> 00:23:39.333
Thinks he can handle everything himself.

454
00:23:39.334 --> 00:23:41.420
[phone buzzing]

455
00:23:43.255 --> 00:23:45.464
- Reenie.
- You still with your brother?

456
00:23:45.465 --> 00:23:46.549
Yeah.

457
00:23:46.550 --> 00:23:49.135
I know you're not big
into taking my legal advice.

458
00:23:49.136 --> 00:23:52.513
but if you're planning
to sniff around Horizon. think again.

459
00:23:52.514 --> 00:23:55.891
<i>They're into some really dark stuff.
and you cannot trust them.</i>

460
00:23:55.892 --> 00:23:59.478
And if Doug's disappearance has something
to do with them. then I would think twice.

461
00:23:59.479 --> 00:24:01.439
- Copy that.
<i>- What does that mean?</i>

462
00:24:01.440 --> 00:24:04.024
That you hear me
and you're gonna ignore what I'm saying?

463
00:24:04.025 --> 00:24:06.695
No. it means I hear you.
but I made a promise to Doug's wife.

464
00:24:07.612 --> 00:24:09.947
He's out there. in danger.
I'm gonna go get him back.

465
00:24:09.948 --> 00:24:12.283
Okay. You do what you gotta do.

466
00:24:12.284 --> 00:24:14.618
Just keep your eyes open.

467
00:24:14.619 --> 00:24:15.704
Will do.

468
00:24:17.122 --> 00:24:18.497
What does Horizon know about this?

469
00:24:18.498 --> 00:24:19.707
They haven't contacted me.

470
00:24:19.708 --> 00:24:21.167
but that doesn't mean anything.

471
00:24:21.168 --> 00:24:23.961
I think it's time we talked to them.
You have a handler?

472
00:24:23.962 --> 00:24:25.754
I don't think that's a good idea.

473
00:24:25.755 --> 00:24:27.256
Listen. if Doug's out there.

474
00:24:27.257 --> 00:24:30.177
we're gonna get him back.
we need to know we're dealing with.

475
00:24:32.053 --> 00:24:33.179
All right.

476
00:24:33.180 --> 00:24:35.973
[♪ tense music playing]

477
00:24:35.974 --> 00:24:38.017
[♪ circus music playing]

478
00:24:38.018 --> 00:24:40.770
[kids clamoring]

479
00:24:42.522 --> 00:24:44.565
[woman] I don't appreciate you being here.

480
00:24:44.566 --> 00:24:47.318
I draw a strict line
between home and work.

481
00:24:47.319 --> 00:24:48.945
You understand that. right. Russell?

482
00:24:49.863 --> 00:24:52.490
- Compartmentalizing?
- Well. this couldn't wait.

483
00:24:52.491 --> 00:24:54.200
- Doug Thompson?
- Yeah.

484
00:24:54.201 --> 00:24:57.536
Horizon's already aware
and taking steps to monitor the situation.

485
00:24:57.537 --> 00:24:58.913
Monitor? You mean mitigate.

486
00:24:58.914 --> 00:25:01.832
Monitor. so as not to inflame a situation.

487
00:25:01.833 --> 00:25:04.502
More importantly. to protect Doug
and his family.

488
00:25:04.503 --> 00:25:06.212
Why exactly wasn't I called in to help?

489
00:25:06.213 --> 00:25:07.671
We've decided to keep you clean.

490
00:25:07.672 --> 00:25:08.964
Too late for that.

491
00:25:08.965 --> 00:25:11.675
I'm aware. Bringing your brother
into this. not the best move.

492
00:25:11.676 --> 00:25:14.553
- No. I'm full of those.
- You're also ignorant to wider concerns.

493
00:25:14.554 --> 00:25:16.681
Why is Moy Solano a target?

494
00:25:17.307 --> 00:25:20.184
- You don't get to ask that question.
- I don't work for you.

495
00:25:20.185 --> 00:25:23.647
But I can make sure that whatever happens
to Doug lands at your feet.

496
00:25:25.232 --> 00:25:27.566
Russ. let's get out of here.
We'll call Reenie.

497
00:25:27.567 --> 00:25:29.735
- Have her keep digging.
- I'd appreciate it

498
00:25:29.736 --> 00:25:32.446
if you kept a tight circle on this
as per your NDA.

499
00:25:32.447 --> 00:25:35.032
Well. NDA is <i>no bueno</i>
now that Doug's been snatched.

500
00:25:35.033 --> 00:25:37.576
- We don't know that.
- I think we do.

501
00:25:37.577 --> 00:25:38.870
What is it about Solano?

502
00:25:39.996 --> 00:25:41.581
Come on. We're not gonna stop.

503
00:25:44.251 --> 00:25:46.835
Solano was funding a rebel organization

504
00:25:46.836 --> 00:25:48.879
trying to overthrow the government.

505
00:25:48.880 --> 00:25:50.464
Who hired you to take him out?

506
00:25:50.465 --> 00:25:51.591
[knocking on window]

507
00:25:51.967 --> 00:25:53.551
[child giggles]

508
00:25:53.552 --> 00:25:55.886
A client with mineral interests
in the country

509
00:25:55.887 --> 00:25:57.806
- they needed to protect.
- Client have a name?

510
00:25:58.723 --> 00:26:01.892
They aren't part of this.
They have nothing to do with Doug.

511
00:26:01.893 --> 00:26:04.437
So it's in your best interests
to sacrifice Doug?

512
00:26:06.523 --> 00:26:10.734
I have to answer up.
Let the situation resolve itself.

513
00:26:10.735 --> 00:26:12.653
Come on.
You gotta give us something.

514
00:26:12.654 --> 00:26:14.280
We're gonna do this regardless.

515
00:26:14.281 --> 00:26:16.407
Please. Where is he?

516
00:26:16.408 --> 00:26:17.867
Where's Doug?

517
00:26:23.164 --> 00:26:26.875
There's the safe house
outside of Richmond.

518
00:26:26.876 --> 00:26:28.962
He could be there. I don't know.

519
00:26:31.923 --> 00:26:32.924
Thank you.

520
00:26:34.175 --> 00:26:35.217
[kids exclaiming]

521
00:26:35.218 --> 00:26:36.385
Kids.

522
00:26:36.386 --> 00:26:38.430
[kids laughing]

523
00:26:45.353 --> 00:26:47.438
[Colter] What are we
walking into here. Russell?

524
00:26:47.439 --> 00:26:50.191
Just a safe house.
Hopefully Doug is okay.

525
00:26:55.030 --> 00:26:57.032
[♪ ominous music playing]

526
00:26:58.450 --> 00:26:59.451
Russ.

527
00:27:07.167 --> 00:27:08.168
[Russell] Clear!

528
00:27:13.757 --> 00:27:14.966
There's no sign of Doug.

529
00:27:16.343 --> 00:27:18.553
If he was here.
he didn't go down without a fight.

530
00:27:29.272 --> 00:27:30.649
Doug was definitely here.

531
00:27:37.030 --> 00:27:39.490
It looks like he was interested
in Carlos Solano.

532
00:27:39.491 --> 00:27:40.658
Moy's brother.

533
00:27:40.659 --> 00:27:42.743
Yeah. Moy was running
the family business

534
00:27:42.744 --> 00:27:44.537
while Carlos has been in prison.

535
00:27:48.249 --> 00:27:50.043
Got out last month.

536
00:27:54.714 --> 00:27:56.924
Carlos is after Doug
for killing his brother.

537
00:27:56.925 --> 00:27:58.885
That's why they waited a year and a half.

538
00:28:00.804 --> 00:28:02.931
They didn't just send one guy here.
They sent three.

539
00:28:04.891 --> 00:28:07.017
If they wanted they'd have
killed him here.

540
00:28:07.018 --> 00:28:09.603
My guess. Carlos wants to kill him
with his own hands.

541
00:28:09.604 --> 00:28:11.146
Great. So where'd they take Doug?

542
00:28:11.147 --> 00:28:13.191
Mmm. That is the question.

543
00:28:13.983 --> 00:28:14.984
That's weird.

544
00:28:18.029 --> 00:28:19.030
Is that a camera?

545
00:28:20.365 --> 00:28:21.448
Yeah.

546
00:28:21.449 --> 00:28:23.410
Let's see if it recorded anything of use.

547
00:28:23.952 --> 00:28:24.952
Nice.

548
00:28:24.953 --> 00:28:26.705
- [keypad clicking]
- [text chimes]

549
00:28:30.333 --> 00:28:33.293
Look. I think it's time
we call in law enforcement.

550
00:28:33.294 --> 00:28:35.796
- [chuckles] That's funny.
- Look around you. man.

551
00:28:35.797 --> 00:28:37.590
We're in over our head.

552
00:28:38.383 --> 00:28:42.386
Colter. Horizon is an above
black ops contractor for the government.

553
00:28:42.387 --> 00:28:44.680
- And they want plausible deniability.
- That's right.

554
00:28:44.681 --> 00:28:47.600
They want to clean up a mess
and they want zero blowback.

555
00:28:48.852 --> 00:28:51.061
It's just you and me. man.
No one's coming for us.

556
00:28:51.062 --> 00:28:54.190
- Hey. if you want to tap out...
- I don't tap out.

557
00:28:55.608 --> 00:28:56.860
I didn't think you would.

558
00:28:58.069 --> 00:29:00.280
I just want you to know
what you're getting into.

559
00:29:04.826 --> 00:29:05.994
[Colter] What you got there?

560
00:29:08.830 --> 00:29:11.958
It's. um... [chuckles]
a knife Dad gave me.

561
00:29:13.376 --> 00:29:16.086
He said it's one of the few things
a man can count on

562
00:29:16.087 --> 00:29:18.173
for protection and shelter and food.

563
00:29:19.090 --> 00:29:20.090
Hmm.

564
00:29:20.091 --> 00:29:22.135
He didn't make you
carry one of these?

565
00:29:23.928 --> 00:29:25.679
- No.
- Yeah. well.

566
00:29:25.680 --> 00:29:28.057
I don't know
why I've kept it all these years.

567
00:29:28.683 --> 00:29:29.975
It's been with me everywhere.

568
00:29:29.976 --> 00:29:32.644
Yeah? And that's the knife
Doug went back for?

569
00:29:32.645 --> 00:29:35.481
I told him it was nothing.
but it has my name on it. so...

570
00:29:35.482 --> 00:29:36.982
[Colter] I get it.
it's important to you.

571
00:29:36.983 --> 00:29:39.110
Not a lot of things
you can count on in life.

572
00:29:42.447 --> 00:29:44.073
It's good to have you back. bro.

573
00:29:48.161 --> 00:29:49.245
I never left.

574
00:29:51.039 --> 00:29:52.415
- You know what I mean.
- Hmm.

575
00:29:56.753 --> 00:29:59.046
So what's. uh...
What's your plan. man?

576
00:29:59.047 --> 00:30:00.506
What's the exit plan here?

577
00:30:00.507 --> 00:30:02.716
[chuckles] I don't...
I don't have one.

578
00:30:02.717 --> 00:30:04.093
Hmm.

579
00:30:05.303 --> 00:30:06.303
- You do?
- Yeah.

580
00:30:06.304 --> 00:30:08.430
I'm gonna open up
a little brewery some place nice.

581
00:30:08.431 --> 00:30:11.016
Have a tasting menu.
A little farm-to-table action.

582
00:30:11.017 --> 00:30:13.560
- It'll be awesome.
- You're joining the food service industry?

583
00:30:13.561 --> 00:30:14.645
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

584
00:30:14.646 --> 00:30:15.813
You've had my beer. It's good.

585
00:30:15.814 --> 00:30:17.690
- Better than good.
- It is. It's good.

586
00:30:19.234 --> 00:30:21.736
Really. no plan?
No... No exit strategy? This is it?

587
00:30:22.654 --> 00:30:25.615
This is it. you know?
Open road.

588
00:30:26.533 --> 00:30:28.325
Wouldn't want
to be anywhere else.

589
00:30:28.326 --> 00:30:30.578
Hmm. Strokes for folks.
I suppose.

590
00:30:31.913 --> 00:30:33.121
[phone buzzing]

591
00:30:33.122 --> 00:30:34.207
Here we go.

592
00:30:35.083 --> 00:30:36.250
Bobby. what do you got?

593
00:30:36.251 --> 00:30:39.002
All the good stuff.
Got the camera footage you wanted.

594
00:30:39.003 --> 00:30:40.170
Anything interesting?

595
00:30:40.171 --> 00:30:42.130
Three guys pulled up
to the safe house

596
00:30:42.131 --> 00:30:43.966
in a blue van
about six hours ago.

597
00:30:43.967 --> 00:30:46.218
But only two of
the same dudes came out.

598
00:30:46.219 --> 00:30:47.344
Anybody with 'em?

599
00:30:47.345 --> 00:30:50.431
Yeah. They're dragging some dude
with a hood pulled over his head.

600
00:30:52.100 --> 00:30:54.309
- They got Doug.
<i>- Not for nothing.</i>

601
00:30:54.310 --> 00:30:55.894
but these guys look like pros.

602
00:30:55.895 --> 00:30:57.729
Only got a partial plate.
but I'm thinking

603
00:30:57.730 --> 00:30:59.690
it belongs to this
Pacora Grove LLC

604
00:30:59.691 --> 00:31:01.066
with only a PO Box listed.

605
00:31:01.067 --> 00:31:02.861
Right. Thanks. Bobby.

606
00:31:11.828 --> 00:31:13.412
Well. well. we meet again.

607
00:31:13.413 --> 00:31:16.081
- Russell.
- Okay. let's focus up. They have Doug.

608
00:31:16.082 --> 00:31:18.917
- I know. Bobby sent me the footage.
- Need to move fast.

609
00:31:18.918 --> 00:31:20.712
- Already on it.
- Of course you are.

610
00:31:21.713 --> 00:31:22.754
I called my friend at the FBI.

611
00:31:22.755 --> 00:31:25.425
and this is what he gave me
on Carlos and Moy Solano.

612
00:31:26.843 --> 00:31:28.510
Giving this to you is a mistake.

613
00:31:28.511 --> 00:31:30.888
But if I didn't.
I figured you would just

614
00:31:30.889 --> 00:31:32.931
break in somewhere.
and you would get caught.

615
00:31:32.932 --> 00:31:35.435
- My weekend would be ruined.
- I would make it up to you.

616
00:31:36.436 --> 00:31:38.562
- Not necessary. really.
- The offer's there.

617
00:31:38.563 --> 00:31:42.941
Okay. The van that took Doug
was registered to a Pacora Grove LLC.

618
00:31:42.942 --> 00:31:45.736
- Any mention of that in here?
- [Reenie] Yeah. actually.

619
00:31:45.737 --> 00:31:48.614
the LLC
belongs to a lieutenant of Carlos Solano.

620
00:31:48.615 --> 00:31:51.158
And he also happens
to own a vacation home

621
00:31:51.159 --> 00:31:52.659
in the Blue Ridge Mountains.

622
00:31:52.660 --> 00:31:54.078
less than three hours from here.

623
00:31:56.247 --> 00:31:57.248
Have fun. boys.

624
00:31:59.417 --> 00:32:00.751
Let's go.

625
00:32:00.752 --> 00:32:03.128
Let's go? Whoa.
What are you doing? You crazy?

626
00:32:03.129 --> 00:32:05.756
This Solano guy. he's gonna have security.
You realize that?

627
00:32:05.757 --> 00:32:08.884
You can't just go in there guns a-blazin'.
You're gonna need backup.

628
00:32:08.885 --> 00:32:10.553
Your backup's gonna need backup.

629
00:32:11.179 --> 00:32:13.597
I got you. You and me.

630
00:32:13.598 --> 00:32:16.141
Come on. we'll go get geared up.
We'll go get Doug.

631
00:32:16.142 --> 00:32:17.226
We'll do it alone.

632
00:32:18.937 --> 00:32:20.146
Come on. man. You good?

633
00:32:22.023 --> 00:32:23.190
Let's go.

634
00:32:23.191 --> 00:32:25.276
[♪ dramatic music playing]

635
00:32:35.995 --> 00:32:37.412
[whispering] Check this out.

636
00:32:37.413 --> 00:32:39.247
They got their own landing strip.

637
00:32:39.248 --> 00:32:41.625
[Russell] That's probably why
they brought Doug here.

638
00:32:41.626 --> 00:32:44.336
So Carlos can kill the man
who killed his brother.

639
00:32:44.337 --> 00:32:45.754
Doug could still be alive.

640
00:32:45.755 --> 00:32:47.464
Let's hope we got here before Carlos.

641
00:32:47.465 --> 00:32:48.883
We got a guard at 11 o'clock.

642
00:32:50.885 --> 00:32:53.304
I got him. I'll be right back.

643
00:33:00.603 --> 00:33:01.688
[struggling]

644
00:33:07.318 --> 00:33:08.318
Well done. Russ.

645
00:33:08.319 --> 00:33:10.113
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

646
00:33:24.335 --> 00:33:27.421
Few more inside.
I still like our odds. though.

647
00:33:27.422 --> 00:33:29.548
- You good?
- I'm good.

648
00:33:29.549 --> 00:33:30.758
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

649
00:33:41.436 --> 00:33:44.063
[sporting event playing indistinctly
on TV]

650
00:33:49.277 --> 00:33:52.822
[commentator speaking indistinctly on TV]

651
00:33:56.117 --> 00:33:58.786
[men chattering in Spanish]

652
00:34:02.165 --> 00:34:04.834
[commentary and chatter
continues in background]

653
00:34:17.847 --> 00:34:19.140
- [gun firing]
- [groans]

654
00:34:22.060 --> 00:34:23.686
[man yelling in Spanish]

655
00:34:24.353 --> 00:34:26.355
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

656
00:34:27.607 --> 00:34:29.025
[men clamoring]

657
00:34:30.568 --> 00:34:32.862
- [flashbang explodes]
- [men screaming]

658
00:34:37.075 --> 00:34:38.284
[guns firing]

659
00:34:50.046 --> 00:34:51.464
- No Doug.
- All right. let's go.

660
00:34:53.591 --> 00:34:55.384
- [Russell grunts]
- [gun firing]

661
00:34:57.553 --> 00:34:58.846
- You good?
- Yeah.

662
00:34:59.764 --> 00:35:00.807
Let's see.

663
00:35:01.682 --> 00:35:04.267
- It's fine. It's just the arm.
- You don't look fine.

664
00:35:04.268 --> 00:35:06.062
I'm fine. Let's go.

665
00:35:06.813 --> 00:35:08.606
- Come on.
- All right.

666
00:35:16.697 --> 00:35:18.657
Hey. that's him. Doug!

667
00:35:18.658 --> 00:35:21.409
- Doug. hey.
- Oh. man! Russ.

668
00:35:21.410 --> 00:35:23.663
I got you. We're gonna
get you out of here. okay?

669
00:35:24.539 --> 00:35:27.457
- What about my wife?
- She's fine. She's fine.

670
00:35:27.458 --> 00:35:29.501
- She's good. Come on.
- I'm sorry. man.

671
00:35:29.502 --> 00:35:31.545
- I know.
- I didn't tell you about Solano.

672
00:35:31.546 --> 00:35:33.797
You're good. You're good.
I got you. all right?

673
00:35:33.798 --> 00:35:35.382
[Doug] He's on his way.

674
00:35:35.383 --> 00:35:37.301
- Come on.
- Yeah. let's go.

675
00:35:38.970 --> 00:35:40.972
[rooster crowing]

676
00:35:43.266 --> 00:35:46.269
All right. Doug. In you go. Easy.

677
00:35:47.145 --> 00:35:48.146
[sighs]

678
00:35:49.105 --> 00:35:50.772
Let me see that.

679
00:35:50.773 --> 00:35:52.149
- It's fine.
- Yeah.

680
00:35:52.150 --> 00:35:54.067
- It's fine!
- All right. come on.

681
00:35:54.068 --> 00:35:56.362
At least let me clean it
and wrap it for you.

682
00:35:57.697 --> 00:35:59.782
Yeah. All right.

683
00:36:01.159 --> 00:36:02.160
[groans]

684
00:36:04.162 --> 00:36:06.164
[wincing]

685
00:36:09.959 --> 00:36:12.002
[Colter] You know the drill here. right?

686
00:36:12.003 --> 00:36:14.296
- It's gonna burn like hell.
- Oh. yeah. just do it.

687
00:36:14.297 --> 00:36:15.506
[Colter] Here we go.

688
00:36:19.552 --> 00:36:21.804
[exhales] Mmm-hmm.

689
00:36:23.014 --> 00:36:24.639
You're enjoying this. aren't you?

690
00:36:24.640 --> 00:36:26.267
- Mmm. a little bit.
- [chuckles]

691
00:36:27.351 --> 00:36:28.643
- Ow! [winces]
- Yup.

692
00:36:28.644 --> 00:36:30.896
You'll have to see a doctor.
You know that. right?

693
00:36:30.897 --> 00:36:32.648
Yeah. I'll do that later.

694
00:36:34.817 --> 00:36:37.027
I'm gonna need you to get
Doug home for me. will you?

695
00:36:37.028 --> 00:36:38.987
What the hell are you talking about?

696
00:36:38.988 --> 00:36:41.490
I got a little unfinished business
I gotta take care of.

697
00:36:43.201 --> 00:36:44.702
Talking about killing Solano?

698
00:36:45.369 --> 00:36:46.786
Come on. man. Don't be dumb.

699
00:36:46.787 --> 00:36:48.830
We got Doug.
We just walk away.

700
00:36:48.831 --> 00:36:51.625
No. I wish it were that easy.

701
00:36:51.626 --> 00:36:53.127
I gotta get back there.

702
00:36:54.253 --> 00:36:56.922
Just like that?
This is goodbye?

703
00:36:56.923 --> 00:36:58.590
Hell. no.

704
00:36:58.591 --> 00:37:01.301
No. no. I'll. uh...
I'll come find you.

705
00:37:01.302 --> 00:37:03.178
Talk about that exit plan of yours.

706
00:37:03.179 --> 00:37:06.224
One that doesn't involve
dragging a trailer all over the country.

707
00:37:07.308 --> 00:37:09.393
- I told you. I'm fine.
- [chuckles] Yeah.

708
00:37:10.728 --> 00:37:12.187
It's very on brand.

709
00:37:12.188 --> 00:37:14.606
[♪ country music playing]

710
00:37:14.607 --> 00:37:16.942
Hey. man. Thank you.

711
00:37:16.943 --> 00:37:18.486
Okay?

712
00:37:20.863 --> 00:37:22.573
I'll see you when I see you.

713
00:37:24.283 --> 00:37:27.827
<i>♪ I saw my face at the water's edge ♪</i>

714
00:37:27.828 --> 00:37:30.331
<i>♪ The man with the heavy heart ♪</i>

715
00:37:31.040 --> 00:37:34.292
<i>♪ But every now and then
He feels so close ♪</i>

716
00:37:34.293 --> 00:37:36.878
<i>♪ And every now and then so far ♪</i>

717
00:37:36.879 --> 00:37:38.297
<i>♪ Tell me... ♪</i>

718
00:37:40.049 --> 00:37:42.510
Hold on a sec. How do I look?

719
00:37:43.928 --> 00:37:46.764
Well. I think... Good. considering.

720
00:37:48.933 --> 00:37:52.144
Honestly. I think she's just gonna be
happy to have you back home.

721
00:37:53.938 --> 00:37:55.773
[both sighing]

722
00:37:57.275 --> 00:37:58.276
[Tracy sniffles]

723
00:38:01.570 --> 00:38:02.571
[Tracy] Thank you.

724
00:38:03.364 --> 00:38:04.657
Just thank you.

725
00:38:06.534 --> 00:38:07.867
Where's Russell?

726
00:38:07.868 --> 00:38:10.078
Uh. I don't really know.

727
00:38:10.079 --> 00:38:13.916
It's hard. isn't it?
The half answers?

728
00:38:15.042 --> 00:38:16.335
You get used to it.

729
00:38:18.170 --> 00:38:19.297
Can you stay for a while?

730
00:38:20.589 --> 00:38:22.758
Thanks. but I gotta...
I gotta go.

731
00:38:24.010 --> 00:38:25.303
Thank you.

732
00:38:26.053 --> 00:38:28.179
I'm so glad you're home.

733
00:38:28.180 --> 00:38:32.392
